abstract="As the overwhelming development of Internet of Things (IoT) in all parts of human lives, there are significantly demanding research and projects of IoT in healthcare area. While many challenges still exist in the specific area, growing concerns of security aspects inevitably arise across variety of IoT products from both academic studies and indus-tries, in difierent types of service classification. This paper describes the current research of IoT in healthcare focused in the aspect of security including authentication, confidentiality, access control, privacy, trust, policy enforcement, middleware, mobile, protocol, and network, followed by comparisons and discussions. Additionally, future works from research and industrial point of view are presented.",
