publisher="Springer International Publishing",
address="Cham",
pages="274--283",
abstract="The Internet of Things (IoT) is changing the industrial sectors, business models and processes. In this context, a special area positively affected by IoT is the prevention of risk factors. A permanently connected network of new products, machines, people and organizations, is a technological advance that can be oriented to combat the risks of fires in places of greater vulnerability in the business areas. This paper presents an application project regarding to a fire prevention system in places where temperature can be measured using the new IoT tools. This project and its novel advantages can be helpful in the development of preventive to increase safety in industry.",
