abstract="The system of collection, transmission and processing of data for wearable sensors for personal health care using the heart rate monitoring, skin temperature and electrophotonic imaging (EIP) sensors is described. EPI instrument based on the stimulation of photon and electron emissions from the surface of the object is used. The paper describes the interaction of the system components, the methods and hardware implementation of data transfer, information about computer software for working with database servers and client terminals as well as components of a remote patient monitoring system based on cloud architecture. Examples of information presented to the patients and doctors are presented.",
