booktitle="Internet of Things, Smart Spaces, and Next Generation Networks and Systems",
year="2017",
publisher="Springer International Publishing",
address="Cham",
pages="206--213",
abstract="Nano-devices with embedded molecular films appear as promising nano communications tools. In general, processing in such hybrid nano-device consists of initial energy of both activated electronic and atomic subsystems of an embedded molecular species, followed by intra- and inter-molecular nanoscale signals generation and reception of the transmitted signal at remote site. Actually, electromagnetic radiation can establish wireless nano communication in Visible, Infrared, and Microwave frequency ranges. In this manuscript, we estimate some properties of a microelectronics receiver in such systems, presented by novel dynamic operation pin photodetector, possesses signal integration, and required for receiving and demodulation of an electromagnetic wave. Revealed both theoretical and experimental characteristics of a photodetector have allowed designing dynamic process scenarios, as well as its possible applications inside a nano network.",
