abstract="As one of important technologies of Internet of Things, Multimedia Wireless Sensor Network(MWSN) has been widely used in all industries. MWSN needs higher bandwidth in MAC layer than traditional WSN. Although AMCP procotol works well in traditional WSN, it is difficult to meet the requirement of multiple-hop MWSN due to its half-duplex mode. Hence, a full-duplex mode is introduced based on the assumption that each node has two radios, and a high-speed multi-hop AMCP algorithm is proposed in this paper. Several data frames can be transmitted after each channel negotiation succeeds to reduce the frequency of channel competition. Simulation results show that the novel algorithm increases 203{\%} compared with that of tranditional AMCP.",
