abstract="The focus of the project is to utilize wireless technologies for unobtrusive, proactive patient healthcare monitoring. Currently, there is a lack of cohesive, integrated, network platforms to monitor and analyze patient activity. This project proposes to fill this need by developing a data-monitoring dashboard to be centered on proactive early detection of lifestyle anomalies for an aging population. The project scope explores the potential for a proactive dashboard to integrate external devices using algorithms to monitor an array of ``core'' behaviors that represent a constellation of stable, predictable and habit-like activities. These core behaviors being Ingestion, Hydration, Gait, and Sleep. The focus of the data-monitoring dashboard would be centered on proactive early detection of lifestyle anomalies and health-care intervention.",
